00:02:21.925 --> 00:02:25.832
I think it's quite transformational to
how we traditionally teach and learn.

00:02:25.832 --> 00:02:28.755
The traditional model
is you have a lecture,

00:02:28.755 --> 00:02:31.920
you have a lecture that normally occurs

00:02:31.920 --> 00:02:35.197
while everyone's in a room
together at some scheduled time.

00:02:35.197 --> 00:02:39.322
Then you have practice in the form of
homework that normally goes on at home,

00:02:39.322 --> 00:02:42.832
usually on your own and if you
get stuck there's not much help

00:02:42.832 --> 00:02:44.257
and you get very little feedback.

00:02:44.257 --> 00:02:46.798
The book might have every
other problems answer,

00:02:46.798 --> 00:02:49.677
but you have no idea why
you got it right or wrong.

00:02:49.677 --> 00:02:53.952
Then you have some type of
assessment, some type of quiz.

00:02:53.952 --> 00:03:00.250
You maybe get 80 or 90% right
on that quiz, you are labeled
a B student or an A student

00:03:00.250 --> 00:03:02.803
and then you move on to the next topic.

00:03:02.803 --> 00:03:04.453
(writing) Next topic.

00:03:04.453 --> 00:03:10.774
And because of this structure, and
it's no individuals fault, it's more
mainly a bi-product of the system,

00:03:10.774 --> 00:03:15.747
everyone has to learn at the
same pace, the lecture is 1
to 30 people at their pace.

00:03:15.747 --> 00:03:19.353
It doesn't matter if half the class
is lost or half the class is bored,

00:03:19.353 --> 00:03:20.932
that's what everyone's getting.

00:03:20.932 --> 00:03:24.128
No matter how good of a teacher you
are you have to cater to everyone,

00:03:24.128 --> 00:03:28.295
so some percentage will be lost
and some percentage will be bored.

00:03:28.295 --> 00:03:32.453
Then no mater whether you
get 10% wrong or 20% wrong

00:03:32.453 --> 00:03:37.337
or 30% wrong as long as you are
"passing" you move on to the next topic.

00:03:37.337 --> 00:03:42.333
Anyone familiar with math or science knows
that if you have some core weakenesses,

00:03:42.333 --> 00:03:46.694
if there's 10% of exponent
problems you didn't know how to do,

00:03:46.694 --> 00:03:49.937
later on when you move
to more advanced topics

00:03:49.937 --> 00:03:53.654
that's going to be a major
hole in your foundation,

00:03:53.654 --> 00:03:58.067
it's going to make it almost impossible
to master more advanced topics.

00:03:58.067 --> 00:03:59.828
So, this is the traditional model.

00:03:59.828 --> 00:04:03.487
What this software is advocating
or maybe what I am advocating,

00:04:03.487 --> 00:04:09.255
